                2. DEFINITIONS AND USER TYPES
                2.1 System Definitions
                System: The RGDC Dental Management System, including the website interface, database, APIs, integrations, and all associated services and features.
                Account: Your unique user profile within the System, protected by login credentials and associated with a specific user type.
                Records: All data stored within the System including but not limited to patient information, dental records, treatment histories, appointments, billing information, and system logs.
                Branch: Any physical location of Reyes-Guansing Dental Clinic operating under the RGDC network.
                2.2 User Types and Access Privileges
                The System recognizes four distinct user types, each with defined access privileges and responsibilities:
                Owner
                Access Level: Full administrative control over all System functions and data
                Privileges: Create, modify, and delete all user accounts; access all patient records across all branches; configure system settings and security parameters; manage branch operations; view comprehensive audit trails and reports; suspend or delete accounts that violate these Terms
                Responsibilities: Ensure System security and compliance; oversee proper use by all users; maintain confidentiality of administrative credentials; make final decisions on policy violations
                Dentist
                Access Level: Clinical record management and patient account oversight
                Privileges: Create and manage patient accounts; access and modify dental records for assigned patients; document treatments and clinical notes; schedule and manage appointments; view and update treatment plans; access patient history for clinical decision-making
                Responsibilities: Ensure accuracy of clinical documentation; maintain patient confidentiality; use System only for legitimate clinical purposes; report any suspected security breaches
                Staff
                Access Level: Administrative support functions
                Privileges: Schedule and manage appointments; update patient contact information; process billing and payments; generate reports; manage clinic calendars; send notifications to patients; perform data entry tasks
                Responsibilities: Maintain accuracy of administrative data; protect patient information; assist patients with account-related questions; follow clinic policies and procedures
                Patient
                Access Level: Limited access to personal information only
                Privileges: View personal dental records and treatment history; access appointment schedules; update personal contact information; view billing statements; receive notifications and reminders; communicate with clinic staff
                Responsibilities: Provide accurate personal and medical information; maintain confidentiality of login credentials; report any unauthorized account access; notify clinic of changes to contact information or medical history
                2.3 Cross-Branch Access
                Access to patient records across different RGDC branches is controlled by role-based permissions. Unless explicitly authorized by an Owner, users are typically limited to accessing records within their assigned branch to maintain appropriate data segregation and security.

                3. ACCOUNT REGISTRATION AND REQUIREMENTS
                3.1 Account Creation
                To use the RGDC Dental Management System, you must create an account by providing accurate, complete, and current information including:
                Full legal name
                Valid email address
                Contact phone number
                Date of birth
                Residential address
                Emergency contact information (for patient accounts)
                Any other information required during the registration process
                For Patient Accounts: Your account will be created by an authorized RGDC Dentist or Staff member during your first visit or through the online registration portal. You will be required to set a secure password upon first login.
                For Staff Accounts: Accounts are created by authorized Owners or designated administrators with appropriate role assignments.
                3.2 Account Verification
                Upon account creation, you may be required to verify your email address by clicking a verification link sent to the email you provided. Unverified accounts may have limited functionality until verification is completed.
                3.3 Mandatory Agreement to Terms
                As specified in Section 1, you must explicitly agree to these Terms and Conditions by checking the acknowledgment box during registration. This requirement addresses the clinic's commitment that "every patient kailangan may consent" to avoid potential legal disputes and ensures all users acknowledge their responsibilities regarding data storage and processing within the System.
                3.4 Password Requirements and Security
                You must create a strong password that meets the following minimum requirements:
                At least 8 characters in length
                Contains at least one uppercase letter
                Contains at least one lowercase letter
                Contains at least one number
                Contains at least one special character (#, $, %, etc.)
                You are solely responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of your password and account credentials. You must:
                Never share your password with others
                Change your password immediately if you suspect unauthorized access
                Log out of your account when using shared or public computers
                Notify RGDC immediately of any suspected security breach
                3.5 Account Accuracy
                You agree to provide accurate, current, and complete information during registration and to promptly update such information to maintain its accuracy. RGDC reserves the right to suspend or terminate accounts that contain false, inaccurate, or incomplete information.

                4. SYSTEM FEATURES AND FUNCTIONALITY
                4.1 Core System Features
                The RGDC Dental Management System provides the following core features based on user type:
                For All Users:
                Secure login and authentication
                Password reset functionality
                Account settings management
                Notification preferences
                For Owners:
                Complete user management across all branches
                System configuration and settings
                Comprehensive reporting and analytics
                Audit trail access
                Security monitoring and controls
                For Dentists:
                Patient record management
                Treatment planning and documentation
                Appointment scheduling
                Clinical notes and progress tracking
                Prescription management
                Access to patient dental history
                For Staff:
                Appointment booking and calendar management
                Patient registration and data entry
                Billing and payment processing
                Report generation
                Email and SMS notification management
                For Patients:
                View personal dental records
                Access appointment history and schedules
                Update contact information
                View treatment plans and recommendations
                Receive appointment reminders
                Access billing statements
                4.2 Google Calendar API Integration
                The System integrates with Google Calendar API to provide appointment synchronization features. By enabling this integration, you authorize the System to:
                Create calendar events for your dental appointments
                Update existing appointment events when changes occur
                Delete calendar events when appointments are cancelled
                Access your Google Calendar to prevent scheduling conflicts
                You can enable or disable this integration at any time through your account settings. Disabling integration will not affect your appointments within the RGDC System but will stop synchronization with your Google Calendar.
                4.3 Gmail API Integration
                The System uses Gmail API to send automated email notifications for:
                Appointment confirmations and reminders
                Treatment updates and follow-up instructions
                Password reset requests
                System announcements and policy updates
                Billing statements and payment receipts
                Security alerts and account notifications
                By creating an account, you consent to receive these automated emails. You can manage notification preferences in your account settings, though certain critical notifications (security alerts, legal notices) cannot be disabled.
                4.4 Record Archival Period
                When any record is deleted from the System—whether patient records, appointments, treatment notes, or user accounts—it enters a 30-day archival period before permanent deletion. During this period:
                The record is marked as "deleted" but remains in the System database
                The record is not visible through normal System operations
                Authorized Owners can restore the record if deletion was made in error
                The record cannot be modified during the archival period
                After 30 days, the record is permanently and irreversibly deleted from all systems and backups
                This archival period provides protection against accidental deletion and allows reasonable time for data recovery requests.
                4.5 Patient Record Deletion
                Patient records can be deleted under the following circumstances:
                Patient requests account closure and record deletion
                Owner determines records should be removed for policy violations
                Legal requirements mandate record deletion
                However, deletion requests are subject to:
                The 30-day archival period described in Section 4.4
                Legal record retention requirements (minimum 10 years for medical records)
                Ongoing legal proceedings or disputes requiring record preservation
                RGDC reserves the right to retain records beyond deletion requests when legally required or when deletion would compromise patient safety or clinic operations.
                4.6 Appointment Management
                The System provides comprehensive appointment scheduling features:
                Real-time availability checking across dentists and branches
                Automated conflict detection
                Appointment reminders via email (24 hours and 1 hour before appointment)
                Rescheduling and cancellation options
                Waitlist management for fully booked time slots
                Cancellation Policy: Patients should cancel or reschedule appointments at least 24 hours in advance when possible. Repeated missed appointments without notice may result in limitations on future booking privileges.
                4.7 Treatment Record Management
                Dentists document all treatments within the System, creating comprehensive records that include:
                Clinical examinations and findings
                Diagnoses and treatment plans
                Procedures performed
                Materials used
                Post-treatment instructions
                Follow-up recommendations
                These records enter the 30-day archival period if deleted but are generally retained for the legally required minimum of 10 years to support continuity of care and emergency reference.
                4.8 Security Features
                The System implements multiple security measures to protect user accounts and patient data:
                Password Encryption: All passwords are encrypted using industry-standard bcrypt hashing algorithms before storage. Passwords are never stored in plain text, and even system administrators cannot view your actual password.
                Role-Based Access Control (RBAC): Access to data and System functions is strictly controlled based on user type. Users can only access information and perform actions appropriate to their assigned role.
                Account Lockout: After 5 consecutive failed login attempts, your account is automatically locked for security purposes. You must contact RGDC support or wait 30 minutes for automatic unlock. This prevents brute force password attacks.
                Session Timeout: User sessions automatically expire after 30 minutes of inactivity, requiring re-authentication. This protects against unauthorized access when devices are left unattended.
                Audit Trails: All significant actions within the System are logged with user identity, timestamp, IP address, and action details. These logs are retained for security monitoring and compliance purposes as detailed in Section 4.12.
                Two-Factor Authentication (Optional): Users may enable two-factor authentication for enhanced account security, requiring both password and a verification code from their mobile device.
                4.9 Communication Features
                The System facilitates communication between users through:
                Automated email notifications for appointments and updates
                Internal messaging between patients and clinic staff (where available)
                Bulk announcements from clinic administration
                Emergency contact notifications
                All communications through the System are subject to monitoring for security and quality assurance purposes.
                4.10 Billing and Payment Features
                The System tracks billing information including:
                Treatment costs and service fees
                Payment history and outstanding balances
                Insurance claims and coverage details
                Payment receipts and statements
                Patients can view their billing history and statements through their account dashboard. Actual payment processing may be handled separately and is subject to the clinic's payment policies.
                4.11 Reporting and Analytics
                Owners and authorized users can generate various reports:
                Appointment statistics and trends
                Patient demographics and visit frequencies
                Treatment outcomes and success rates
                Financial reports and revenue analysis
                System usage and performance metrics
                Reports containing patient information are subject to the same confidentiality and access control requirements as the underlying data.
                4.12 Audit Trails and Compliance Logging
                The System maintains comprehensive audit trails for compliance with healthcare regulations and data privacy laws:
                Logged Activities:
                All user login and logout events
                Patient record access (viewing, editing, creation)
                Appointment creation, modification, and deletion
                Treatment record documentation
                User account changes and administrative actions
                System configuration changes
                Security events and alerts
                Audit Trail Retention: Audit logs are retained for a minimum of 3 years for compliance purposes and may be retained longer if required by legal proceedings or regulatory investigations.
                Audit Trail Access: Only Owners and authorized system administrators can access audit trails. Audit logs cannot be modified or deleted by any user, ensuring integrity for compliance and legal purposes.

