                Gmail API: We utilize Gmail API to send automated email notifications including appointment confirmations, reminders, treatment updates, system announcements, and password reset requests. This integration allows for reliable, timely delivery of important communications.
                Third-Party Privacy Policies: These third-party services operate under their own privacy policies and terms of service. While we carefully select reputable service providers and require them to maintain appropriate security measures, we are not responsible for their privacy practices. We encourage you to review:
                Google Privacy Policy: https://policies.google.com/privacy
                Google Terms of Service: https://policies.google.com/terms
                Data Minimization with Third Parties: We share only the minimum information necessary for these services to function. Third parties do not receive access to your complete medical records, treatment details, or other sensitive health information beyond what is essential for their specific service.
                External Links: Our website may contain links to external resources such as insurance provider portals, dental product information, or educational content. These external websites are not operated by RGDC and are not covered by this Privacy Policy. We are not responsible for the content, privacy practices, or security of external websites. When you click on external links, you leave our system and should review the privacy policies of those sites.
                Service Provider Agreements: All third-party service providers with access to patient information operate under contractual agreements that require them to maintain confidentiality, implement appropriate security measures, use data only for authorized purposes, comply with Philippine data privacy laws, and immediately report any security incidents.

                11. CHILDREN'S PRIVACY
                The RGDC Dental Management System provides dental healthcare services to patients of all ages, including minors (individuals under 18 years of age in the Philippines):
                Parental Consent Required: For patients under 18 years of age, we require a parent or legal guardian to create and manage the account. During registration, the parent or guardian must provide their own contact information and explicitly consent to the collection and processing of their child's personal and health information.
                Guardian Responsibilities: Parents and legal guardians are responsible for:
                Providing accurate information about their child
                Managing their child's account settings and preferences
                Reviewing their child's dental records and treatment plans
                Authorizing appointments and treatments
                Ensuring their child's account credentials remain secure
                Updating information as their child grows and circumstances change
                Access to Minor's Information: Parents and legal guardians have full access to their child's dental records, appointment history, and all other account information through their linked guardian account. This access continues until the child reaches 18 years of age, at which point the account can be transitioned to the now-adult patient's independent control.
                Limited Independent Use: Minors may be given supervised access to view their own appointment schedules and basic information, but cannot make changes to records, schedule appointments independently, or access billing information without parental oversight.
                Protecting Children's Information: We implement the same rigorous security measures to protect children's information as we do for adult patients. We do not use children's information for marketing purposes or share it with third parties except as described in this Privacy Policy and with parental consent.
                Transition to Adult Status: When a patient reaches 18 years of age, we can assist in transitioning the account from parental control to the patient's independent control. This process requires verification of the patient's identity and age, and the patient must agree to our Terms and Conditions and Privacy Policy independently.

                12. INTERNATIONAL DATA TRANSFERS
                While RGDC primarily operates within the Philippines, certain aspects of our system may involve international data transfers:
                Cloud Infrastructure: Our system may utilize cloud hosting services with data centers located in various countries. When your information is stored or processed outside the Philippines, we ensure that service providers maintain data protection standards equivalent to or exceeding Philippine requirements under Republic Act No. 10173.
                Third-Party Services: Google Calendar and Gmail services are provided by Google LLC, a US-based company with global infrastructure. When you enable integration with these services, your appointment information and email address may be processed on servers located outside the Philippines.
                Data Protection Safeguards: For any international data transfers, we implement appropriate safeguards including:
                Contractual clauses requiring equivalent data protection standards
                Encryption of data in transit and at rest
                Access controls limiting who can view or process data
                Regular audits of service provider security practices
                Compliance with international data protection frameworks
                Your Rights Remain Protected: Regardless of where your data is physically stored or processed, you retain all privacy rights granted under Philippine law, including the right to access, correct, and delete your information, and the right to file complaints with the National Privacy Commission.

                13. CHANGES TO THIS PRIVACY POLICY
                RGDC reserves the right to update, modify, or replace this Privacy Policy at any time to reflect changes in our practices, legal requirements, technological developments, or system enhancements. We are committed to keeping you informed about how we protect your privacy:
                Notification of Changes: When we make significant changes that materially affect how we collect, use, or protect your personal information, we will notify you through:
                Email notification sent to the address associated with your account using our Gmail API integration
                Prominent notice displayed on your dashboard when you log into the system
                An updated "Last Updated" date at the top of this Privacy Policy
                Minor Updates: For minor, non-material changes such as clarifications, formatting improvements, or updated contact information, we may update this policy without direct notification. However, the "Last Updated" date will always reflect the most recent changes.
                Review Period: After notification of significant changes, you will have a reasonable period (typically 30 days) to review the updated policy before it takes effect. During this period, your continued use of the system under the previous policy terms will remain valid.
                Acceptance of Changes: By continuing to use the RGDC Dental Management System after the effective date of the updated Privacy Policy, you acknowledge that you have read, understood, and agree to be bound by the revised terms. Your continued use constitutes acceptance of the changes.
                Right to Object: If you disagree with significant changes to this Privacy Policy, you have the right to:
                Contact us to discuss your concerns
                Request account closure and deletion of your data, subject to our legal record retention obligations
                File a complaint with our Data Privacy Officer or the National Privacy Commission
                Version Control: We maintain historical versions of our Privacy Policy for reference. You may request access to previous versions by contacting our Data Privacy Officer.
                Regular Reviews: We conduct periodic reviews of this Privacy Policy to ensure it remains current, accurate, and compliant with evolving data privacy laws and healthcare regulations.

